Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a pale red-orange ribbed vessel, the fabric is relatively coarse and contains many small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and faint traces of at least ten lines of Coptic (?) text written in black ink.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393850) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393850)
